Flow Designer
....................................................................................

Enable process automation 

All > Process Automation > Flow Designer 

....................................................................................

Diagramming View:
    Trigger Types:
        Record, Date, Inbound, Service Catalog, SLA Task 
        
    Flow Logic Types:
        Call a workflow 
        Do following in parallel 
        Dynamic Flows 
        Else if 
        End Flow 
        For Each 
        Get Flow Outputs 
        If 
        Set Flow variables
        Wait for a duration of time 

....................................................................................

Triggers:
    Record Based
    Date Based
    Application based 

....................................................................................

Flow Components:
    Triggers 
    Conditions
    Actions:
        Executed by System 
        Core Actions:
            Ask for Approval 
            Create record 
            Delete Record 
            Lookup Record 
            Wait for COndition 

    Data:
        Data pills -> drag and drop 
        created for each action result

    Integration Hub:
        Pre built set of Integration actions -> Spokes
        third party app interaction
....................................................................................

Process Automation Designer: (PAD)
    Enable cross-enterprise workflows and single unified process
    Create Process Definition, Activate, System -> process Execution 

....................................................................................

Virtual Agent:
    Obtain information, make decision and perform common task 
